OL,3,CPlasterer jailed over two Facebook
OL,4,Cposts inciting racial hatred
OL,6,FNorth Wales Police was made aware of
OL,7,Ftwo racist posts published on
OL,8,FFacebook, supporting recent riots, on
OL,9,F10 August.
OL,11,FPolice said one of the posts incited
OL,12,Frioting at a number of properties in
OL,13,Fthe Deeside area.
OL,15,FA judge, who praised the police and
OL,16,FCrown Prosecution Service for acting
OL,17,Fswiftly, told Kingsley he was a
OL,18,F"bigot" who had committed his crime
OL,19,Ffrom the "comfort" of his home
OL,20,Falthough he had not been physically
OL,21,Finvolved.
